ny exceptions thrown appropriately. I’ll need to think more about how this might affect my testing strategy.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Typing variables in code**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about adding type annotations to all my variables. It feels like a solid way to improve code readability and maintainability. I want to do one-to-one annotations and focus specifically on the test file for the active class. This approach should lead to cleaner code and help with debugging down the line. Let’s get started on writing those annotations! It feels like the right thing to do for better organization.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_IZUYKSW4iH5SVzL6in7QFTbo|fc_045013a6bfbfdceb0169f2d017a05c81939f1108ca2342b3c7\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_jackson/ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_jackson;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.util.EnumMap;\\nimport java.util.EnumSet;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.util.ClassUtil;\\n\\npublic class ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void locatesEnumTypeFromEmptyEnumSetMetadata() {\\n        EnumSet<EncodingMode> emptyModes = EnumSet.noneOf(EncodingMode.class);\\n\\n        assertResolvedEnumType(() -> ClassUtil.findEnumType(emptyModes));\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void locatesEnumTypeFromEmptyEnumMapMetadata() {\\n        EnumMap<EncodingMode, String> emptyNames = new EnumMap<>(EncodingMode.class);\\n\\n        assertResolvedEnumType(() -> ClassUtil.findEnumType(emptyNames));\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void assertResolvedEnumType(EnumTypeLookup lookup) {\\n        try {\\n            Class<? extends Enum<?>> enumType = lookup.findEnumType();\\n\\n            assertThat(enumType).isSameAs(EncodingMode.class);\\n        } catch (IllegalArgumentException ex) {\\n            assertThat(ex).hasCauseInstanceOf(IllegalAccessException.class);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private enum EncodingMode {\\n        PLAIN,\\n        DICTIONARY\\n    }\\n\\n    @FunctionalInterface\\n    private interface EnumTypeLookup {\\n        Class<? extends Enum<?>> findEnumType();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_jackson/ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest.java\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_jackson;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.util.EnumMap;\\\\nimport java.util.EnumSet;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\n\\\\nimport shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.util.ClassUtil;\\\\n\\\\npublic class ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest {\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void locatesEnumTypeFromEmptyEnumSetMetadata() {\\\\n        EnumSet<EncodingMode> emptyModes = EnumSet.noneOf(EncodingMode.class);\\\\n\\\\n        assertResolvedEnumType(() -> ClassUtil.findEnumType(emptyModes));\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void locatesEnumTypeFromEmptyEnumMapMetadata() {\\\\n        EnumMap<EncodingMode, String> emptyNames = new EnumMap<>(EncodingMode.class);\\\\n\\\\n        assertResolvedEnumType(() -> ClassUtil.findEnumType(emptyNames));\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static void assertResolvedEnumType(EnumTypeLookup lookup) {\\\\n        try {\\\\n